		<td><b>Re: Replicating Ninja Gaiden II Fade Out</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah, there's a very prominent 60hz buzz as Startropics fades out music. (You can hear something similar in Super Mario Bros. between levels.)<br /><br />My favourite way to do it was with a DPCM sample to ramp to a specific value, but then play it back at a tuned pitch (the samplerates come in a partial A440-tuned scale) at the same time as that pitch is being played in the song.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


